---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use — JamJet"
  description="JamJet terms of use for the website and open-source software."
  canonical="https://jamjet.dev/terms/"
>

<div class="legal">
  <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
  <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: March 2026</p>

  <h2>Open-source software</h2>
  <p>
    The JamJet runtime, SDKs, and CLI are open-source software licensed under the
    <a href="https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Apache License 2.0</a>.
    Your use of the software is governed by that license.
  </p>

  <h2>Website</h2>
  <p>
    The jamjet.dev website is provided for informational purposes. We make reasonable efforts to
    keep content accurate, but documentation, benchmarks, and examples may lag behind the latest
    release. When in doubt, the source code is authoritative.
  </p>

  <h2>Benchmarks</h2>
  <p>
    Performance benchmarks published on this site reflect specific hardware, software versions,
    and configurations described in each benchmark. Results will vary in different environments.
    All benchmark code is published for independent reproduction.
  </p>

  <h2>Examples and code</h2>
  <p>
    Code examples on this website and in our GitHub repositories are provided under the same
    Apache 2.0 license unless otherwise noted. They are intended as starting points, not
    production-ready applications.
  </p>

  <h2>Trademarks</h2>
  <p>
    "JamJet" and the JamJet logo are trademarks of JamJet Labs. Third-party product names
    mentioned on this site (LangGraph, CrewAI, AutoGen, OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.) are trademarks
    of their respective owners.
  </p>

  <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
  <p>
    The software is provided "as is", without warranty of any kind. See the Apache 2.0 license
    for the full limitation of liability and disclaimer of warranties.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about these terms: <a href="mailto:hello@jamjet.dev">hello@jamjet.dev</a>.
  </p>
</div>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 24px 6rem;
  }
  .legal h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .legal-updated {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  .legal h2 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .legal p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .legal a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .legal a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
